fields.title: Battle: Los Angeles
fields.comments: I enjoyed the premise. It's just an urban war movie where the baddies happen to be aliens. There is very little science fiction. The special effects on the ground were good, but the wide cityscapes could've used a bit more polish. The character work before the s hit the f was entirely unnecessary, but brief enough. I cannot rightly apprehend the confusion of ideas that could provoke such a casting choice as Michelle Rodriguez for a tough-girl character when doing so has been a joke for more than a decade.

fields.title: Insidious
fields.comments:
Dan trachtenberg. scariest movie ever.

Not as scary as I would expect. The early subtle scares were good, but then they just "showed too much" and it became more strange than scary. By the end, it was almost laughable.

fields.title: Moneyball
fields.comments: Pitt's character is interesting. Not sure what I think of Jonah Hill in this type of role; if he can eventually break out of his typecast I guess we'll be able to really judge him as an actor. The topic of the film (using statistics to assemble a winning MLB team on a budget by finding undervalued players) is fascinating, but there wasn't enough detail in the film to offset my utter apathy towards sports. I was confused throughout by the passage of time.
